OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1776175862
OL,3,CSouthport report finds failures by
OL,4,Cauthorities - and at home
OL,6,FBut there are searching questions too
OL,7,Fabout access to online materials for
OL,8,Fchildren, the availability of weapons
OL,9,Fand the complexities of the attacker's
OL,10,Fautism (the Chair is keen not to
OL,11,Fstigmatise others with condition).
OL,13,FUltimately, only the attacker can
OL,14,Faccount for his crimes. But for the
OL,15,Ffamilies of the victims and survivors,
OL,16,Ftoday's report contains the painful
OL,17,Fconclusion that he could ` and should
OL,18,F` have been stopped.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/6
